CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 6, 1957, pg. A6, reads: "All-City Westinghouse Musicians - During an interval at last Monday's concert at Oakland's Carnegie Music Hall, Paquita Sharp, a Junior Courier reporter, was the center of the conversation of fellow Westinghouse students who, like her, had been chosen to play in all-city high school orchestra. Miss Sharp was one of the orchestra's first-chair flutists. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Westinghouse High School jazz ensemble members, from left: Nelson Harrison, Janson Kelly, Paquita Sharp, Alton Harris, and Paul Hord, in Carnegie Music Hall for All-City high school band concert
